<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04929</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING DEVELOPERS OF PROPOSED CONDOMINIUM PROJECTS TO DEVELOP AN AREA FOR SOCIALIZED HOUSING, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 4726 ENTITLED "THE CONDOMINIUM ACT"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to help mitigate, if not eradicate the backlog of housing needs in the country by requiring
developers of proposed condominium projects to develop an area for socialized housing which is
equivalent to twenty percent (20%) of the total project area or total condominium project cost, at the option of the developer.

Prescribes that the area for such socialized housing component shall be done within the same city
or municipality, whenever feasible, and in accordance with the standards set by the Housing and
Land Use Regulatory Board (HLURB) and other existing laws.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>HERRERA-DY, BERNADETTE &quot;BH&quot;</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT ON 2019-10-02</td></tr></table>